Localisation is an ongoing process, it doesn‚Äôt have an end. However, it does have a beginning. And the best kind of beginning is when all of the stakeholders get together at the start of the localisation process and discuss what‚Äôs going to happen, how and when.Good localisation partners should lead this process, after all this is their specialism. Fine-tuning the tone of voice for each market, compiling a glossary of important terms, running training sessions with linguists to become familiar with the brands, products and services‚Ä¶a lot of these important activities can be completed upfront and can actually help drive the process forward. However, what‚Äôs important is that the communication channels are left open throughout so that everyone remains engaged and can contribute. This collaborative effort is the key to efficient and successful localisation campaigns.  #xl8 #l10n #translation #localisation #brand #marketing #teamwork #teamAJT #translatebythesea #newquay #cornwall
